From Jim Perkowski Subject Re jiggers In article susan susan writes a friend of mine has a very severe cause of jiggers for over a year now they cause him a lot of i recently read i don't know where about a possible cure for does anyone have any information on this i can't remember the name of the treatment or where i read I'll probably get flamed for this but when I was a kid we would go to my uncles cabin on Middle Bass Island on Lake We always came home with a nasty case of jiggers large red bumps where the buggers had burrowed into the skin My mother would paint the bumps with clear finger nail This was repeated daily for about a week or The application of the polish is supposed to suffocate them as it seals of the All I can say is it worked for One word of caution Putting finger nail polish on a jigger bite stings like If I do get flamed for this just put jam in my pockets and call me kentcomm and kentcomm